notes: Represents either N (asparagine) or D (aspartic acid) - will translate it as D based on higher occurence (N willl be off by one base only)
Represents either L (leucine) or I (isoleucine)  - will translate it as L based on higher occurence (I willl be off by one base only)
Represents either E (Glutamic acid) or Q (Glutamine)  - will translate it as E based on higher occurence (Q willl be off by one base only)
